> +		unsigned long type = strtoul(argv[2], NULL, 16);
> +		unsigned long expected = strtoul(argv[3], NULL, 16);

If this test is invoked manually with missing arguments, such as
"./hwcap_inherit verify", will strtoul() dereference a NULL pointer?

The condition only checks that argc > 1, so argv[2] and argv[3] could
be NULL when passed to strtoul(). Could we add an explicit check to
ensure argc >= 4 before accessing these arguments?

